IBADAN – The Oyo State Independent Electoral Commission (OYSIEC), in preparation ahead of the May 15 local government election has assured political parties in the state of a free and fair election. OYSIEC made this known while addressing members of Action Democratic Party (ADP) during the primary election held in Ibadan. HOW NIGERIAN MEN CAN NOW NATURALLY STOP PREMATURE EJACULATION, LOW SPERM COUNT AND OTHER MEN'S SEXUAL NEEDS. MADAM ALWAYS WANTS IT BIGGER, STRONGER AND LONG-LASTING!!! OYSIEC chairman, Barrister Isiaka Olagunjure, represented by OYSIEC commissioners, Mr Emmanuel Olarenwaju and Prince Afeez Adeniyi, said the Commission is keen on ensuring that all political parties are equally treated in the forth coming election. “It is not possible for us to be bias, as we all know, the governor is empowered by law to constitute an electoral commission as Gov Makinde have not done beyond establishing the commission and it is an independent commission which is not under the control of the governor. IGP Orders Full Investigation Into Plot To Assassinate Ned Nwoko Road Accidents Claim 29 Lives In 2 Months In Osun – FRSC “With this, I can assure you that we are keen in ensuring that all political parties are equally treated as we want them to participate fully and Action Democratic Party have done that in ensuring that they conducted their primary election in a peaceful environment.” Speaking at the event, Apostle Dare Ojo, Chairman, Action Democratic Party, Oyo State, applauded the OYSICE representatives for a transparent act of election and believe things are to change during their regime. He added that Action Democratic Party, Oyo State is ready to take part of the election as they are set to kick of their campaigns in Oyo state “We have met with OYSIEC chairman and other commissioners, we have been assured of credible and fair election, we will believe that things are to change in their time” “ADP is ready to take part in the election. We have done our primaries and OYSIES is happy with the way we conducted ourselves.”